    "problemStatement": "You are given an array AAA of length NNN.\n\nDetermine the count of subarrays of AAA which contain their length as an element.\n\nFormally, count the number of pairs (L,R)(L, R)(L,R) (1\u2264L\u2264R\u2264N)(1\\le L\\le R\\le N)(1\u2264L\u2264R\u2264N) such that: (R\u2212L+1)\u2208{AL,AL+1,\u2026,AR}(R-L+1) \\in \\{A_L, A_{L+1}, \\ldots, A_R\\}(R\u2212L+1)\u2208{AL\u200b,AL+1\u200b,\u2026,AR\u200b}.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nFirst line will contain TTT, number of test cases. Then the test cases follow.\nFirst line of each test case contains an integer NNN denoting the length of the array AAA.\nSecond line of each test case contains NNN space-separated integers A1,A2,\u2026,ANA_1, A_2, \\ldots, A_NA1\u200b,A2\u200b,\u2026,AN\u200b - denoting the array AAA.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output the count of subarrays containing their lengths.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u226410001 \\leq T \\leq 10001\u2264T\u22641000",
      "1\u2264N\u22642\u22c51051 \\leq N \\leq 2 \\cdot 10^51\u2264N\u22642\u22c5105",
      "1\u2264Ai\u2264N1 \\leq A_i \\leq N1\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264N",
      "Sum of NNN over all test cases does not exceed 5\u22c51055 \\cdot 10^55\u22c5105."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "3\n3\n1 2 1\n5\n2 3 1 3 5\n10\n10 7 4 4 2 9 2 1 9 3",
        "output": "4\n6\n15",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nTest Case 111: There are 444 subarrays (i,j)(i,j)(i,j) containing their lengths. They are (1,1),(1,2),(2,3),(1,1), (1,2), (2,3),(1,1),(1,2),(2,3), and (3,3)(3,3)(3,3).\nTest Case 222: There are 666 subarrays (i,j)(i,j)(i,j) containing their lengths. They are (1,2),(1,3),(1,5),(2,4),(3,3),(1,2), (1,3), (1,5), (2, 4), (3,3),(1,2),(1,3),(1,5),(2,4),(3,3), and (3,5)(3,5)(3,5)."
      }
    ]
